The replies are not JUnit focused. So, I apologize ahead of time. Perhaps we
should have this conversation outside the JUnit mailing list ?

&gt;&quot;real&quot; programmers
I am curious, how do you identify them ? :-)

&gt;Java applet, so I&#39;ve focused on finding out how to use JUnit to test them

An applet really spans multiple layers of the architecture. There is the GUI
stuff and then there is the model of the data stuff. Different testing tools
apply to different layers of the archictecture.

&gt;sample projects to show me if I just do it the right way

I offer my temperature converter. I am a beginner in Java and did a
temperature converter to teach myself this stuff. Take a look at
http://www.ypl.com/resume/ch02s03.html and see if that helps.

&gt;You&#39;ll never really put the applet in a JFrame

You extend the JApplet class.
(http://www.ypl.com/java/mvc/bergin_joseph/lucente_robert/html/17_17/ch17s17
s05s01.html)

Consider reading up on SWING top level containers
(http://java.sun.com/docs/books/tutorial/uiswing/components/toplevel.html)

&gt;Refactor the applet so that it&#39;s a thin shell around the content and the
business logic

If you want to impress your friends at a party, use the buzz word Model View
Control design pattern.

For example for my temperature converter, I did the following

1) Temperature model in 1 class
(http://www.ypl.com/java/mvc/bergin_joseph/lucente_robert/html/17_17/ch17s17
s01s01.html). Used JUnit to test this.
(http://www.ypl.com/java/mvc/bergin_joseph/lucente_robert/html/17_17/ch17s17
s02s01.html)

2) Displaying of the data placed in 1 package
(http://www.ypl.com/java/mvc/bergin_joseph/lucente_robert/html/17_17/ch17s17
s03.html). Don&#39;t worry about strategy design pattern or any of the other
stuff.

3) Control (glue to hold view and data together) put in 1 class
(http://www.ypl.com/java/mvc/bergin_joseph/lucente_robert/html/17_17/ch17s17
s04s01.html)

The other members of the mailing list will be able to provide guidance on
testing display and control.

&gt;Applets have several getters for external information

Watch the security here. Applets have certain restrictions unless you ....
Why are you using the Applet architecture ? As another person said, why not
a stand alone app ?

&gt;Applets have several getters for external information

Start simple user param

1) HTML file w/ param
(http://www.ypl.com/java/mvc/bergin_joseph/lucente_robert/html/17_17/ch17s17
s06s01.html)

2) Reading of params
(http://www.ypl.com/java/mvc/bergin_joseph/lucente_robert/html/17_17/ch17s17
s05s01.html)

Please note that I am not a Java expert but the above should get you
started.

